The paper focuses on the use of sequence to sequence (Seq2Seq) models for communication in adversarial settings, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of signaling theory, which is a concept from game theory (cs.GT) and the learning process of actor-critic Seq2Seq based agents, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SI).
